primary_outcome.description:
Clinical improvement within 10 days since start of treatment, defined as a decrease of at least 1 point within 10 days from baseline on a six-point ordinal scale:
Not hospitalized/discharged;
Hospitalized, not requiring supplemental oxygen;
Hospitalized, requiring supplemental oxygen;
Hospitalized, requiring nasal high-flow oxygen therapy, noninvasive mechanical ventilation, or both;
Hospitalized, requiring invasive mechanical ventilation, extra-corporeal membrane oxygenation (ECMO), or both; and
Death.

secondary_outcome.description:
Number of days for subject that have a reduction by at least 2 point from baseline on a six point ordinal scale:
Not hospitalized/discharged;
Hospitalized, not requiring supplemental oxygen;
Hospitalized, requiring supplemental oxygen;
Hospitalized, requiring nasal high-flow oxygen therapy, noninvasive mechanical ventilation, or both;
Hospitalized, requiring invasive mechanical ventilation, extra-corporeal membrane oxygenation (ECMO), or both; and
Death.
